# Inside a `"`-delimited literal a literal double-quote is written `\"` (the
# active delimiter is the only `\`-escape besides `\@{`). Here `f"say \"@{w}\""`
# yields the text  say "…"  with the word interpolated, HTML-attribute-escaped.
